Most of the viral infections occurred within the first 4 months from allo-HCT. There were no differences in the median patient age and median time from allo-HCT to specific viral infection, with respective values ranging from 0.4 to 3.8 months. Only in cases of VZV, HSV and NoV were late infections observed, with a median time 6.5, 7.4 and 7.9 months, respectively (
 
